1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,233
<i>Can we please not turn
my mother in yet?</i>

2
00:00:02,233 --> 00:00:04,700
<i>- A lot of people died, Liam.
- I know.</i>

3
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:07,200
<i>Can you let me stay
with her for a bit?</i>

4
00:00:08,033 --> 00:00:09,533
<i> Just one last time.</i>

5
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> Our last meal together.</i>

6
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:14,433
<i> Me, Mama, and Papa.</i>

7
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:17,067
<i>I will bring La Playa Roja
back to life.</i>

8
00:00:17,067 --> 00:00:19,367
<i>I will open a new restaurant
at the resort.</i>

9
00:00:19,367 --> 00:00:21,400
<i> Yes, a lot has happened,</i>

10
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,767
<i>but Olsen and I have more
good memories there.</i>

11
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:24,933
<i> All of us do.</i>

12
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:27,400
<i>I'm impressed
with you too, Jacinto.</i>

13
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,533
<i>You got shot,
fell from a building,</i>

14
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:32,133
<i> but you're still alive.</i>

15
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:34,567
<i>Let's see if you can still
get out of this one.</i>

16
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,067
<i>- Ambush!
- [TIRE EXPLODES]</i>

17
00:00:36,067 --> 00:00:38,333
[TIRES SCREECHING]

18
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:44,667
[SMOKE HISSING]

19
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:46,400
[GUNSHOTS]

20
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:47,567
[COUGHING]

21
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:55,667
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

22
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,467
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [GRUNTS, GROANS]

23
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:03,600
[GUNSHOTS]

24
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:21,667
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

25
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:29,767
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:37,600
[VAN DOOR SLIDES]

27
00:01:39,267 --> 00:01:46,200
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

28
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:07,767
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

29
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:29,867
[OMINOUS MUSIC SWELLING]

30
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:41,167
[GUNSHOTS]

31
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:42,600
Lucas!

32
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:45,333
[GUNSHOTS]

33
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,500
Lucas!

34
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:51,133
- [SCREAMING]
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]

35
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:57,200
[GUNSHOTS]

36
00:02:58,167 --> 00:03:01,233
[GUNSHOTS]

37
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:02,267
[THUD]

38
00:03:02,733 --> 00:03:09,667
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,900
[GUNSHOTS]

40
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,333
[HOMER] Bro!

41
00:03:27,933 --> 00:03:29,233
Bro! [WHIMPERS]

42
00:03:29,233 --> 00:03:30,533
Bro!

43
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:33,900
[HOMER WAILS] Bro!

44
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:35,400
Lucas!

45
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:37,833
Bro! [WHIMPERS]

46
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:39,167
Bro!

47
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,833
Bro! [WHIMPERS]

48
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:44,267
[WAILS] Bro!

49
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:47,200
Bro!

50
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:50,700
[HOMER] Bro!

51
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:52,767
Bro!

52
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,400
[HOMER SCREAMING]

53
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:00,933
Bro!

54
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:10,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:04:53,867 --> 00:05:00,800
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:05,667
[GRETA] Magnus?

57
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,833
[GRETA SIGHS]

58
00:05:18,733 --> 00:05:21,433
Wendy probably thinks
I'll run away again.

59
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:28,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:31,633
[SIGHS]

61
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,633
I can't believe...

62
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:37,767
...I'm coming back
to this place again.

63
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,633
But...

64
00:05:42,867 --> 00:05:44,033
...I have no choice.

65
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:48,767
You know, for me, Greta...

66
00:05:51,767 --> 00:05:53,567
...we always have a choice.

67
00:05:55,933 --> 00:05:56,967
Magnus.

68
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,900
The right choice...

69
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:03,333
...is to keep
what we did a secret

70
00:06:03,967 --> 00:06:05,767
so there will still be
something left for Liam.

71
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:08,533
That's the right decision.

72
00:06:12,033 --> 00:06:13,367
[EXHALES]

73
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,933
Call Lieutenant Areza.

74
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,900
Turn me in to him.

75
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:25,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

76
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,933
- [HANDCUFFS RATTLING]
- [EMIL GROANS]

77
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:31,033
[GRUNTS]

78
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:34,833
[JACINTO] Emil.

79
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:37,600
Man.

80
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,767
I'm sorry for everything
that happened.

81
00:06:43,067 --> 00:06:44,900
We went through
a lot together, didn't we?

82
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:47,800
Maybe we can
still talk this through?

83
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,800
I can help you.

84
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:54,000
Emil, no, please.

85
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,900
- Give me the gun.
- [JACINTO] Emil, no.

86
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:00,167
[JACINTO WHIMPERS]

87
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:01,567
- [GUN COCKS]
- Emil...

88
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:03,867
Please, Emil. Don't do this.

89
00:07:04,767 --> 00:07:08,633
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GRUNTS]

90
00:07:08,633 --> 00:07:15,567
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:21,700
[PHONE BUZZING]

92
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,767
Boss.

93
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:24,467
[PHONE BUZZING]

94
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:25,500
This is Areza's phone.

95
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:32,667
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [PHONE BUZZING]

96
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,567
[MAGNUS] Lieutenant Areza.

97
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:45,333
Sir?

98
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:47,000
[MAGNUS]<i> My wife
</i> is with me right now.

99
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:50,100
We're here at...

100
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,067
25 Kings Road...

101
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,967
<i> Alicante.</i>

102
00:07:54,967 --> 00:08:01,933
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:21,467
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:25,033
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

105
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:31,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:41,500
The police are on their way.

107
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,267
You know, I thought...

108
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:51,067
...you wouldn't be able
to turn in your own mother.

109
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,100
I believe that crimes...

110
00:08:58,767 --> 00:09:00,000
...must be paid for.

111
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:04,067
Rich or poor...

112
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:06,833
...related by blood or not.

113
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:09,967
Bro, justice...

114
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:12,300
...treats everyone equally.

115
00:09:15,633 --> 00:09:17,567
But if you were in my position,

116
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,300
would you do the same?

117
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,167
Would you do what's right?

118
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:29,133
[CHUCKLES SLIGHTLY]

119
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:31,600
[CLEARS THROAT]

120
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,700
The question is...

121
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,100
What is right? What is wrong?

122
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:40,600
I lost my mother...

123
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:42,933
...for a decade.

124
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,967
So if I were in your position,
it feels like...

125
00:09:50,633 --> 00:09:52,867
I wouldn't be able
to turn her in.

126
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,900
I can't lose her again.

127
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,767
That's where we differ.

128
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:07,667
You grew up
with your whole family.

129
00:10:07,667 --> 00:10:08,800
But me...

130
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:12,633
I didn't even get to know
my real father,

131
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,400
and my mother was taken
from me.

132
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:18,133
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

133
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:20,900
You've met your father.

134
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,733
Homer Sebastian.

135
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:29,133
I wish I hadn't.

136
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,667
I hope you like the leche flan.

137
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:38,167
[CHUCKLES]

138
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:48,200
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

139
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,133
Boss?

140
00:11:00,867 --> 00:11:02,633
- Boss?
- [LENI] Gwen.

141
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:07,233
- Just come with me.
- Where are we going?

142
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:09,700
I've got Leni with me,
what's the plan, boss?

143
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:11,900
<i> Pa, where are you?</i>

144
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,833
We need to stop this, Pa.

145
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,733
Before we all run out.

146
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:17,067
We're close, dear.

147
00:11:18,133 --> 00:11:19,700
This is the last mission.

148
00:11:20,933 --> 00:11:23,000
To find your sister, Ayen.

149
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,367
<i> Pa, come on!</i>

150
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:26,000
Even now?

151
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,733
Tell me, where are we
going to find her?

152
00:11:28,733 --> 00:11:30,467
Magnus knows.

153
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:32,033
I'll squeeze it out of him.

154
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:34,200
<i> Gwen...</i>

155
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,033
...follow us,
it's dangerous there.

156
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:39,667
Pa, for heaven's sake,
enough!

157
00:11:39,867 --> 00:11:41,033
- Hello?
- Let's go, Leni.

158
00:11:41,067 --> 00:11:42,300
- Papa--
- Come on.

159
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:44,233
- Where are we going, Gwen?
- Go inside.

160
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:52,233
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

161
00:12:18,067 --> 00:12:19,233
[GRETA] Wow.

162
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,333
There's dessert too.

163
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:25,400
Two minutes,
it just needs to chill.

164
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:12:28,933 --> 00:12:32,300
Looks like Areza's
on the way too.

166
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,367
So...

167
00:12:33,367 --> 00:12:39,833
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:42,033
Son...

169
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,967
thank you for preparing
my favorite.

170
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:54,100
Somehow, I'll be happy...

171
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:02,000
...that this is how it all ends.

172
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:12,067
I'll be separated
from you and your dad.

173
00:13:13,433 --> 00:13:16,100
But I know you'll be okay.

174
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,833
You'll be fine.

175
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:24,767
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:45,933
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:08,933
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

178
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:25,900
[CAMERA CLICKING]

179
00:14:35,967 --> 00:14:41,567
[CAMERA CLICKING]

180
00:14:41,567 --> 00:14:42,733
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:50,433
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]

182
00:14:55,800 --> 00:15:00,000
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:06,933
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

184
00:15:13,067 --> 00:15:14,400
I'm sorry, son.

185
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:19,933
I failed to give you
a complete family.

186
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,433
That's my fault.

187
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,467
Sorry.

188
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,333
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:29,833
To be honest, Ma...

190
00:15:32,533 --> 00:15:35,967
I don't think I should be
feeling this way.

191
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,967
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:15:37,967 --> 00:15:39,200
That something is missing
in my life.

193
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,400
Because there isn't.

194
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:45,533
Grandpa Ben has always
been there for me.

195
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,300
Even Sir Magnus.

196
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:55,067
Did you fall in love
with him, Ma?

197
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,767
How about...

198
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:10,467
Homer?

199
00:16:10,467 --> 00:16:11,500
My father.

200
00:16:14,367 --> 00:16:15,300
Yes.

201
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:17,500
I tried...

202
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:20,500
during that time.

203
00:16:22,367 --> 00:16:23,833
But when...

204
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,933
I was pregnant with you,

205
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:30,000
I didn't tell him.

206
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:33,300
I saw...

207
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,400
how cruel a person he is.

208
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:41,300
What could they be doing now?

209
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:45,200
For sure,
they're enjoying their millions.

210
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:47,567
How fortunate.

211
00:16:48,533 --> 00:16:49,500
Ma.

212
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,600
For real?

213
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,000
Why?

214
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:56,100
The bad guys always win

215
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:58,900
and indulge in their riches.

216
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,067
And they get away
with their crimes.

217
00:17:00,067 --> 00:17:01,067
Not really.

218
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,167
Justice finds its way.

219
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:06,400
Just look at Ma'am Greta.

220
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:08,300
Right?

221
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:16,300
We're leaving.

222
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:18,233
Don't go in anymore.
It's useless.

223
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,300
We'll be okay now.

224
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:23,133
Let's wait for the police.

225
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:26,233
I want to be sure.

226
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:29,400
I want to see them arrest Greta.

227
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,667
Is this really the justice
we've been waiting for?

228
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:35,267
It doesn't seem like it.

229
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:41,000
I was also imprisoned.

230
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:46,633
Is that enough for all
the bad things she has done?

231
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:49,267
I've been in jail too, son.

232
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:51,467
We eat on time.

233
00:17:52,567 --> 00:17:54,433
We have a comfortable bed.

234
00:17:55,433 --> 00:17:56,567
There's even a mattress.

235
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,467
[VOICE BREAKING] Is that enough?

236
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:02,967
Will that punishment be enough?

237
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:10,100
I thought you had forgiven her.

238
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:16,533
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:23,100
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- [OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,567
It's delicious.

241
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:31,500
Have some food, Ma.

242
00:18:32,467 --> 00:18:33,467
[LIAM] Come on.

243
00:18:34,233 --> 00:18:39,567
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

244
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:40,967
Good?

245
00:18:42,567 --> 00:18:48,633
- [SIREN WAILING]
- [SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:18:48,633 --> 00:18:54,967
[SIREN WAILING IN THE DISTANCE]

247
00:18:57,567 --> 00:18:58,633
[ENGINE REVS]

248
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:10,233
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:32,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:37,933
They're here.

251
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:44,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:06,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

253
00:20:15,867 --> 00:20:17,100
<i> They're here.</i>

254
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:19,900
<i>The mastermind of the
La Playa Roja siege has escaped.</i>

255
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:23,167
<i>That's why we're here,
to make sure they're okay.</i>

256
00:20:23,167 --> 00:20:26,200
<i>So you're my real boss,
Ma'am Greta.</i>

257
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,367
<i> You've got the money.</i>

258
00:20:27,367 --> 00:20:29,367
<i> My daughter, Ayen...</i>

259
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:30,433
[SLAP]

260
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:33,267
<i>- You witch! Damn you!
- Aah!</i>

261
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:35,333
<i>Tell me,
where is Ayen?!</i>

262
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:36,867
- [GUNSHOT]
- [SCREAMS]

263
00:20:36,867 --> 00:20:38,133
<i> Is he really my son?</i>

264
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,967
<i> Don't hurt our son.</i>

265
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:42,033
<i>Don't tell me
we're siding with them.</i>

266
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:44,233
<i>Who exactly is our enemy,
Olsen?</i>

267
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:48,300
<i>The Rojas who take advantage
of the poor and the weak?</i>

268
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:52,133
<i>Or those who were exploited
just like us?!</i>

269
00:20:52,133 --> 00:20:56,600
<i> The next bullet is going
</i>straight into your son's chest.

270
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,133
[GUNSHOTS]
